Ex. No: — Merge Multiple Datasets and Perform Data Alignment using Pandas
Aim

To merge multiple datasets using Pandas.

Theory

Merging combines data from multiple tables using common keys.

Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda Distribution
•
Jupyter Notebook / IDLE / Google Colab
•
Pandas Library

Program
import pandas as pd

# Student details dataset
student_details = {
    'Student_ID': [101, 102, 103, 104],
    'Name': ['Ravi', 'Anu', 'Kumar', 'Divya'],
    'Department': ['AI&DS', 'CSE', 'ECE', 'AI&DS']
}

df_students = pd.DataFrame(student_details)

# Student marks dataset
student_marks = {
    'Student_ID': [101, 102, 104, 105],
    'Marks': [85, 90, 88, 76]
}

df_marks = pd.DataFrame(student_marks)

print("Student Details:")
print(df_students)

print("\nStudent Marks:")
print(df_marks)

# Merge operation
merged_df = pd.merge(df_students,
                     df_marks,
                     on='Student_ID')

print("\nMerged Dataset:")
print(merged_df)



